Name: TET
About the game: Prepare a meal for the Vietnamese Lunar New Year dinner. But hurry, your guests are arriving soon! A short hand-drawn experience full of delicious surprises. TET is a fresh and colorful cooking game. Enter the world of delicious Vietnamese food through a series of mini games. Cut the tofu, wash the cabbage, delicately roll the spring rolls, and discover the secrets of the tasty recipes. TET was created by Charlotte Broccard, a Swiss-Vietnamese illustrator and game designer, with the desire to share her cultural heritage. With special thanks to game developers Etienne Frank, Guillaume Mezino, Mario von Rickenbach, and Michael Frei for their support. Initiated at ECAL, University of Art and Design Lausanne.
Developers: Charlotte Broccard,Etienne Frank,Guillaume Mezino,Mario von Rickenbach
